reviews: Lasted me for my entire lifetime of my iPhone 7 Plus. If you break it you can email them for a replacement, but you have to pay a small fee for shipping I believe, so roughly $5-10. I got replacements twice, which gives great value as Otter Box is a good company for customer support.

review_title: Not what I thought it would be
reviews: It doesn't really work. I thought it worked the first time I tried it, but I don't think it's working anymore. Not really a big fan of the under the tongue dissolving.

It was somewhat difficult to install, it took me like more than an hour. It fit perfectly, and FaceID had no problem. There also seems to be perfect touch screen sensitivity and the Apple Pencil works fine. When i finished putting it on, I found a little scuff on the screen on the very top right, but it's not very visible which is ok. it's really frustrating if you are like a clean freak where you dont want any dust lol.
